The paper discusses the use of Fisher information and Shannon entropy in the study of complex systems modeled by isotropic pairwise Gaussian Markov random fields. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SI), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and systems and control (cs.SY). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
